# IINA plugin conventions (youtube-safari)

## Runtime

This plugin runs inside IINA's embedded JS runtime. The global `iina` object provides `core`, `mpv`, `global`, `menu`, `sidebar`, `standaloneWindow`, `file`, `console`, `preferences`, and `utils`. This is not Node.js or a standard browser environment.

## Build (Parcel)

Parcel produces four targets into `dist/`:

| Target | Source | Output | Context |
|--------|--------|--------|---------|
| Player entry | `src/index.ts` | `dist/index.js` | IINA player |
| Global entry | `src/global.ts` | `dist/global.js` | IINA global |
| Sidebar shell | `src/sidebar/shell.ts` | `dist/sidebar/shell.js` | Webview (browser) |
| Parse core | `src/sidebar/parse-core.ts` | `dist/sidebar/parse-core.js` | Node (unit tested) |

Manifest: `Info.json` — `entry`, `globalEntry`, `sidebarTab`, `preferencesPage`.

Sidebar HTML (`sidebar/shell.html`) must reference `../dist/sidebar/shell.js` (IINA webview relative-path rules).

## Script paths

Resolve bash helper scripts via `utils.resolvePath()`. Prefer relative defaults like `scripts/resolve.sh` over hardcoded `~/Projects/youtube-safari/scripts/...` in new code.

Key scripts: `resolve.sh`, `list-formats.sh`, `refresh-cookies.sh`, `list-playlist.sh`, `youtubejs-feed.sh`.

## Commands

```bash
npm run build    # Parcel + syntax check
npm test         # parse-core unit tests (requires build)
npm run watch    # Parcel watch
scripts/install.sh   # build + iina-plugin link
scripts/audit.sh     # full macOS integration audit
```

## IINA launch guardrails

Do not regress patterns checked by `scripts/audit.sh`:

- `mpv.addHook` and `onMessage("openYouTubeWatch")` registered before `playerReady` post
- `menu.forceUpdate()` only via `scheduleMenuForceUpdate` in `native-menus.ts`
- No `setTimeout(enableMenuUpdates)` bootstrap
- No top-level `menu.addItem` in `index.ts`
- Idle dock bootstrap deferred to `iina.window-loaded`
- No global idle last-watch bootstrap in `global.ts`
- `on_load` calls `next` in `finally`; guard shutdown with `isShuttingDown`
- Global entry opens standalone panel, does not call `createPlayerInstance`

After substantive changes: `npm run build && npm test`. Full validation: `scripts/audit.sh` on studio-m4-max.

